                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13937139" author="dpfister" created="Sun, 16 Mar 2014 13:19:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to initialize auxiliary HTTPS connector only after having started the server.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13942243" author="fmeschbe" created="Thu, 20 Mar 2014 20:38:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for providing the patch. I actually took a different route: The server will be started at first and then the connectors will be started one after the other. Any connector not being able to start will prevent the other connector from starting. If neither connector can be started, the Jetty server itself is stopped again.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13942271" author="fmeschbe" created="Thu, 20 Mar 2014 21:03:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in Rev. 1579733 &amp;amp; 1579739:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Start connectors individually after the server start&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Stop the server if no connector can be started&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13943252" author="dpfister" created="Fri, 21 Mar 2014 17:14:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good, thank you for fixing this!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
